<paragraph blockId="6.[189,342,1808,1834]" box="[189,342,1808,1834]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,1808,1834]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1808,1834]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1855,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[189,454,1855,1881]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eudendriidae" genus="Eudendrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="ramosum">
<emphasis box="[189,454,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Eudendrium ramosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered as a cosmopolitan species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouillon J. &amp; Gravili C. &amp; Pages F. &amp; Gili J. M. &amp; Boero F." box="[1000,1268,1855,1882]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 591" refId="ref20033" refString="Bouillon J., Gravili C., Pages F., Gili J. M. &amp; Boero F. 2006. An Introduction to Hydrozoa. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris 194: 1 - 591." type="journal article" year="2006">
Bouillon 
<emphasis box="[1114,1177,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, but many records are likely doubtful (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramil F. &amp; Vervoort W." box="[518,803,1891,1918]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref24650" refString="Ramil F. &amp; Vervoort W. 1992. Report on the Hydroida collected by the &quot; BALGIM &quot; expedition in and around the Strait of Gibraltar. Zoologische Verhandelingen, Leiden 277: 1 - 262." type="journal article" year="1992">Ramil &amp; Vervoort 1992</bibRefCitation>
; Marques 
<emphasis box="[928,987,1891,1917]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
2000). 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert P." box="[1079,1283,1891,1917]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" pagination="59" refId="ref25550" refString="Schuchert P. 2012. North-West European Athecate Hydroids and their Medusae. In: Crothers J. H. &amp; Haywars P. J. (eds) Synopses of the British Fauna (New Series) 59. Field Studies Council, London." type="book chapter" year="2012">Schuchert (2012)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that all records outside the East Atlantic (Arctic to 
<collectingCountry box="[815,970,1927,1953]" name="South Africa" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, including the Mediterranean) need confirmation. The bathymetrical distribution of the species extends from intertidal areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Ansin Agis J." pageId="6" pageNumber="55" refId="ref19347" refString="Ansin Agis J. 1992. Hidrozoos de la Ria de Vigo. PhD thesis, Universidad de Vigo, Spain." type="book" year="1992">Ansín Agís 1992</bibRefCitation>
) to a depth of 
<quantity box="[420,509,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8699999999999999" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="1870.0">1870 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ramil F. &amp; Vervoort W." box="[524,807,1998,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref24650" refString="Ramil F. &amp; Vervoort W. 1992. Report on the Hydroida collected by the &quot; BALGIM &quot; expedition in and around the Strait of Gibraltar. Zoologische Verhandelingen, Leiden 277: 1 - 262." type="journal article" year="1992">Ramil &amp; Vervoort 1992</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
